wiki.content: "Give It Away" is a song by American alternative rock band Red Hot Chili Peppers, released in 1991 on their studio album Blood Sugar Sex Magik. "Give It Away" was the first of five singles from the album and achieved fame around the world. It won a Grammy Award in 1992. Cleveland's Rock and Roll Hall of Fame museum has "Give It Away" listed as one of the 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll. track.name: Give It Away
comments: I like how the guitar part at the end is a reference to Black Sabbath's "Sweet Leaf", then UGK turned around and re-referenced this song in "Pocket Full of Stones (Pimp C Remix)". Its like a chain of reference and every stop along the way is awesome.
Those reversed guitar solos in the middle still give me goosebumps.
